02:18 PM Called 22CF09 scheduled for PH. Defendant, Elizabeth Rachelle Waskosky, appeared in person with Attorney Daniel James Chapman by zoom video.  Attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt appeared for the State in person.  Def confirms she has discussed PH with Attny by video, and waives right to have Attny in person.  Attny Chapman request to proceed by video.  State notes concern with video to see witness, Attny Chapman has no concerns on identity of witness.  Case is on for preliminary hearing.  State calls first witness, Detective Travis Thiex, who is sworn in and testifies.  Venue is made.  Witness has identified the defendant.  No objection from Attny Chapman today.  Court notes identification is made. No other questions from the State. Attny Chapman questions the witness. State redirects. Attny Chapman objects.  Court asks for a rephrase.  State rephrases question.  State continues questioning Detective Thiex.  Attny Chapman objects, irrelevant.  Court overrules.  Detective Thiex continues answering, objection relevance, Court notes relevant, overruled.  Detective Travis Thiex continues, State has no further questions.  Attny Chapman has no further questions.  Witness steps down.  State has no further witnesses.  Attny has no witnesses today.  State provides argument, including party to a crime. Attny Chapman provides argument, should not be bound over, not a felony matter.  Court notes it is not the courts job to say if it is a felony.  Court finds probable cause that a crime has been committed and the defendant probably committed it.  The matter is bound over for further proceedings.  Bond continues. Arraignment scheduled for June 16, 2022 at 10:45 am.
